ga:userType.name: User Type
ga:userType.description: A boolean, either New Visitor or Returning Visitor, indicating if the users are new or returning.

ga:sessionCount.name: Count of Sessions
ga:sessionCount.description: The session index for a user. Each session from a unique user will get its own incremental index starting from 1 for the first session. Subsequent sessions do not change previous session indices. For example, if a user has 4 sessions to the website, sessionCount for that user will have 4 distinct values of '1' through '4'.

ga:daysSinceLastSession.name: Days Since Last Session
ga:daysSinceLastSession.description: The number of days elapsed since users last visited the property, used to calculate user loyalty.

ga:userDefinedValue.name: User Defined Value
ga:userDefinedValue.description: The value provided when defining custom user segments for the property.

ga:userBucket.name: User Bucket
ga:userBucket.description: Randomly assigned users tag to allow A/B testing and splitting of remarketing lists. Ranges from 1-100.

ga:users.name: Users
ga:users.description: The total number of users for the requested time period.

ga:newUsers.name: New Users
ga:newUsers.description: The number of sessions marked as a user's first sessions.

ga:1dayUsers.name: 1 Day Active Users
ga:1dayUsers.description: Total number of 1-day active users for each day in the requested time period. At least one of ga:nthDay, ga:date, or ga:day must be specified as a dimension to query this metric. For a given date, the returned value will be the total number of unique users for the 1-day period ending on the given date.

ga:7dayUsers.name: 7 Day Active Users
ga:7dayUsers.description: Total number of 7-day active users for each day in the requested time period. At least one of ga:nthDay, ga:date, or ga:day must be specified as a dimension to query this metric. For a given date, the returned value will be the total number of unique users for the 7-day period ending on the given date.

ga:14dayUsers.name: 14 Day Active Users
ga:14dayUsers.description: Total number of 14-day active users for each day in the requested time period. At least one of ga:nthDay, ga:date, or ga:day must be specified as a dimension to query this metric. For a given date, the returned value will be the total number of unique users for the 14-day period ending on the given date.

ga:30dayUsers.name: 30 Day Active Users
ga:30dayUsers.description: Total number of 30-day active users for each day in the requested time period. At least one of ga:nthDay, ga:date, or ga:day must be specified as a dimension to query this metric. For a given date, the returned value will be the total number of unique users for the 30-day period ending on the given date.

ga:sessionsPerUser.name: Number of Sessions per User
ga:sessionsPerUser.description: The total number of sessions divided by the total number of users.

ga:percentNewSessions.name: % New Sessions
ga:percentNewSessions.description: The percentage of sessions by users who had never visited the property before.

ga:sessionDurationBucket.name: Session Duration
ga:sessionDurationBucket.description: The length (returned as a string) of a session measured in seconds and reported in second increments.

ga:bounces.name: Bounces
ga:bounces.description: The total number of single page (or single interaction hit) sessions for the property.

ga:sessionDuration.name: Session Duration
ga:sessionDuration.description: Total duration (in seconds) of users' sessions.

ga:uniqueDimensionCombinations.name: Unique Dimension Combinations
ga:uniqueDimensionCombinations.description: Unique Dimension Combinations counts the number of unique dimension-value combinations for each dimension in a report. This lets you build combined (concatenated) dimensions post-processing, which allows for more flexible reporting without having to update your tracking implementation or use additional custom-dimension slots. For more information, see https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/7084499.

ga:hits.name: Hits
ga:hits.description: Total number of hits for the view (profile). This metric sums all hit types, including pageview, custom event, ecommerce, and other types. Because this metric is based on the view (profile), not on the property, it is not the same as the property's hit volume.

ga:bounceRate.name: Bounce Rate
ga:bounceRate.description: The percentage of single-page session (i.e., session in which the person left the property from the first page).

ga:avgSessionDuration.name: Avg. Session Duration
ga:avgSessionDuration.description: The average duration (in seconds) of users' sessions.

ga:hostname.name: Hostname
ga:hostname.description: The hostname from which the tracking request was made.

ga:pagePath.name: Page
ga:pagePath.description: A page on the website specified by path and/or query parameters. Use this with hostname to get the page's full URL.

ga:pagePathLevel1.name: Page path level 1
ga:pagePathLevel1.description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths in the first hierarchical level in pagePath.

ga:pagePathLevel2.name: Page path level 2
ga:pagePathLevel2.description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths in the second hierarchical level in pagePath.

ga:pagePathLevel3.name: Page path level 3
ga:pagePathLevel3.description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths in the third hierarchical level in pagePath.

ga:pagePathLevel4.name: Page path level 4
ga:pagePathLevel4.description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths into hierarchical levels. Up to 4 pagePath levels maybe specified. All additional levels in the pagePath hierarchy are also rolled up in this dimension.

ga:pageTitle.name: Page Title
ga:pageTitle.description: The page's title. Multiple pages might have the same page title.

ga:landingPagePath.name: Landing Page
ga:landingPagePath.description: The first page in users' sessions, or the landing page.

ga:secondPagePath.name: Second Page
ga:secondPagePath.description: The second page in users' sessions.

ga:exitPagePath.name: Exit Page
ga:exitPagePath.description: The last page or exit page in users' sessions.

ga:previousPagePath.name: Previous Page Path
ga:previousPagePath.description: A page visited before another page on the same property, typically used with the pagePath dimension.

ga:pageDepth.name: Page Depth
ga:pageDepth.description: The number of pages visited by users during a session. The value is a histogram that counts pageviews across a range of possible values. In this calculation, all sessions will have at least one pageview, and some percentage of sessions will have more.

ga:pageValue.name: Page Value
ga:pageValue.description: The average value of this page or set of pages, which is equal to (ga:transactionRevenue + ga:goalValueAll) / ga:uniquePageviews.

ga:entrances.name: Entrances
ga:entrances.description: The number of entrances to the property measured as the first pageview in a session, typically used with landingPagePath.

ga:pageviews.name: Pageviews
ga:pageviews.description: The total number of pageviews for the property.

ga:uniquePageviews.name: Unique Pageviews
ga:uniquePageviews.description: Unique Pageviews is the number of sessions during which the specified page was viewed at least once. A unique pageview is counted for each page URL + page title combination.

ga:timeOnPage.name: Time on Page
ga:timeOnPage.description: Time (in seconds) users spent on a particular page, calculated by subtracting the initial view time for a particular page from the initial view time for a subsequent page. This metric does not apply to exit pages of the property.

ga:exits.name: Exits
ga:exits.description: The number of exits from the property.

ga:entranceRate.name: Entrances / Pageviews
ga:entranceRate.description: The percentage of pageviews in which this page was the entrance.

ga:pageviewsPerSession.name: Pages / Session
ga:pageviewsPerSession.description: The average number of pages viewed during a session, including repeated views of a single page.

ga:avgTimeOnPage.name: Avg. Time on Page
ga:avgTimeOnPage.description: The average time users spent viewing this page or a set of pages.

ga:exitRate.name: % Exit
ga:exitRate.description: The percentage of exits from the property that occurred out of the total pageviews.

ga:totalEvents.name: Total Events
ga:totalEvents.description: The total number of events for the profile, across all categories.

ga:uniqueEvents.name: Unique Dimension Combinations
ga:uniqueEvents.description: The definition of `ga:uniqueEvents` will change soon to more accurately reflect the number of unique events. Please use `ga:uniqueDimensionCombinations` instead if you want to retain the existing definition. For more information, see https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/7084499.

ga:eventValue.name: Event Value
ga:eventValue.description: Total value of events for the profile.

ga:sessionsWithEvent.name: Sessions with Event
ga:sessionsWithEvent.description: The total number of sessions with events.

ga:avgEventValue.name: Avg. Value
ga:avgEventValue.description: The average value of an event.

ga:eventsPerSessionWithEvent.name: Events / Session with Event
ga:eventsPerSessionWithEvent.description: The average number of events per session with event.

ga:goalCompletionLocation.name: Goal Completion Location
ga:goalCompletionLocation.description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal completion.

ga:goalPreviousStep1.name: Goal Previous Step - 1
ga:goalPreviousStep1.description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal, one step prior to the goal completion location.

ga:goalPreviousStep2.name: Goal Previous Step - 2
ga:goalPreviousStep2.description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal, two steps prior to the goal completion location.

ga:goalPreviousStep3.name: Goal Previous Step - 3
ga:goalPreviousStep3.description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal, three steps prior to the goal completion location.

ga:goalXXStarts.name: Goal XX Starts
ga:goalXXStarts.description: The total number of starts for the requested goal number.

ga:goalStartsAll.name: Goal Starts
ga:goalStartsAll.description: Total number of starts for all goals defined in the profile.

ga:goalXXCompletions.name: Goal XX Completions
ga:goalXXCompletions.description: The total number of completions for the requested goal number.

ga:goalCompletionsAll.name: Goal Completions
ga:goalCompletionsAll.description: Total number of completions for all goals defined in the profile.

ga:goalXXValue.name: Goal XX Value
ga:goalXXValue.description: The total numeric value for the requested goal number.

ga:goalValueAll.name: Goal Value
ga:goalValueAll.description: Total numeric value for all goals defined in the profile.

ga:goalValuePerSession.name: Per Session Goal Value
ga:goalValuePerSession.description: The average goal value of a session.

ga:goalXXConversionRate.name: Goal XX Conversion Rate
ga:goalXXConversionRate.description: Percentage of sessions resulting in a conversion to the requested goal number.

ga:goalConversionRateAll.name: Goal Conversion Rate
ga:goalConversionRateAll.description: The percentage of sessions which resulted in a conversion to at least one of the goals.

ga:goalXXAbandons.name: Goal XX Abandoned Funnels
ga:goalXXAbandons.description: The number of times users started conversion activity on the requested goal number without actually completing it.

ga:goalAbandonsAll.name: Abandoned Funnels
ga:goalAbandonsAll.description: The overall number of times users started goals without actually completing them.

ga:goalXXAbandonRate.name: Goal XX Abandonment Rate
ga:goalXXAbandonRate.description: The rate at which the requested goal number was abandoned.

ga:date.name: Date
ga:date.description: The date of the session formatted as YYYYMMDD.

ga:year.name: Year
ga:year.description: The year of the session, a four-digit year from 2005 to the current year.

ga:month.name: Month of the year
ga:month.description: Month of the session, a two digit integer from 01 to 12.

ga:week.name: Week of the Year
ga:week.description: The week of the session, a two-digit number from 01 to 53. Each week starts on Sunday.

ga:day.name: Day of the month
ga:day.description: The day of the month, a two-digit number from 01 to 31.

ga:hour.name: Hour
ga:hour.description: A two-digit hour of the day ranging from 00-23 in the timezone configured for the account. This value is also corrected for daylight savings time. If the timezone follows daylight savings time, there will be an apparent bump in the number of sessions during the changeover hour (e.g., between 1:00 and 2:00) for the day per year when that hour repeats. A corresponding hour with zero sessions will occur at the opposite changeover. (Google Analytics does not track user time more precisely than hours.)

ga:minute.name: Minute
ga:minute.description: Returns the minutes, between 00 and 59, in the hour.

ga:nthMonth.name: Month Index
ga:nthMonth.description: The index for a month in the specified date range. In the date range, the index for the first month is 0, for the second month 1, and so on.

ga:nthWeek.name: Week Index
ga:nthWeek.description: The index for each week in the specified date range. The index for the first week in the date range is 0, for the second week 1, and so on. The index corresponds to week entries.

ga:nthDay.name: Day Index
ga:nthDay.description: The index for each day in the specified date range. The index for the first day (i.e., start-date) in the date range is 0, for the second day 1, and so on.

ga:nthMinute.name: Minute Index
ga:nthMinute.description: The index for each minute in the specified date range. The index for the first minute of the first day (i.e., start-date) in the date range is 0, for the next minute 1, and so on.

ga:dayOfWeek.name: Day of Week
ga:dayOfWeek.description: Day of the week, a one-digit number from 0 (Sunday) to 6 (Saturday).

ga:dayOfWeekName.name: Day of Week Name
ga:dayOfWeekName.description: Name (in English) of the day of the week.

ga:dateHour.name: Hour of Day
ga:dateHour.description: Combined values of ga:date and ga:hour.

ga:yearMonth.name: Month of Year
ga:yearMonth.description: Combined values of ga:year and ga:month.

ga:yearWeek.name: Week of Year
ga:yearWeek.description: Combined values of ga:year and ga:week.

ga:isoWeek.name: ISO Week of the Year
ga:isoWeek.description: ISO week number, where each week starts on Monday. For details, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_week_date. ga:isoWeek should only be used with ga:isoYear because ga:year represents Gregorian calendar.

ga:isoYear.name: ISO Year
ga:isoYear.description: The ISO year of the session. For details, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_week_date. ga:isoYear should only be used with ga:isoWeek because ga:week represents Gregorian calendar.

ga:isoYearIsoWeek.name: ISO Week of ISO Year
ga:isoYearIsoWeek.description: Combined values of ga:isoYear and ga:isoWeek.

ga:nthHour.name: Hour Index
ga:nthHour.description: The index for each hour in the specified date range. The index for the first hour of the first day (i.e., start-date) in the date range is 0, for the next hour 1, and so on.

ga:referralPath.name: Referral Path
ga:referralPath.description: The path of the referring URL (e.g., document.referrer). If someone places on their webpage a link to the property, this is the path of the page containing the referring link.

ga:fullReferrer.name: Full Referrer
ga:fullReferrer.description: The full referring URL including the hostname and path.

ga:campaign.name: Campaign
ga:campaign.description: For manual campaign tracking, it is the value of the utm_campaign campaign tracking parameter. For AdWords autotagging, it is the name(s) of the online ad campaign(s) you use for the property. If you use neither, its value is (not set).

ga:source.name: Source
ga:source.description: The source of referrals. For manual campaign tracking, it is the value of the utm_source campaign tracking parameter. For AdWords autotagging, it is google. If you use neither, it is the domain of the source (e.g., document.referrer) referring the users. It may also contain a port address. If users arrived without a referrer, its value is (direct).

ga:medium.name: Medium
ga:medium.description: The type of referrals. For manual campaign tracking, it is the value of the utm_medium campaign tracking parameter. For AdWords autotagging, it is cpc. If users came from a search engine detected by Google Analytics, it is organic. If the referrer is not a search engine, it is referral. If users came directly to the property and document.referrer is empty, its value is (none).

ga:sourceMedium.name: Source / Medium
ga:sourceMedium.description: Combined values of ga:source and ga:medium.

ga:keyword.name: Keyword
ga:keyword.description: For manual campaign tracking, it is the value of the utm_term campaign tracking parameter. For AdWords traffic, it contains the best matching targeting criteria. For the display network, where multiple targeting criteria could have caused the ad to show up, it returns the best matching targeting criteria as selected by Ads. This could be display_keyword, site placement, boomuserlist, user_interest, age, or gender. Otherwise its value is (not set).

ga:adContent.name: Ad Content
ga:adContent.description: For manual campaign tracking, it is the value of the utm_content campaign tracking parameter. For AdWords autotagging, it is the first line of the text for the online Ad campaign. If you use mad libs for the AdWords content, it contains the keywords you provided for the mad libs keyword match. If you use none of the above, its value is (not set).

ga:socialNetwork.name: Social Network
ga:socialNetwork.description: The social network name. This is related to the referring social network for traffic sources; e.g., Google+, Blogger.

ga:hasSocialSourceReferral.name: Social Source Referral
ga:hasSocialSourceReferral.description: A boolean, either Yes or No, indicates whether sessions to the property are from a social source.

ga:campaignCode.name: Campaign Code
ga:campaignCode.description: For manual campaign tracking, it is the value of the utm_id campaign tracking parameter.

ga:organicSearches.name: Organic Searches
ga:organicSearches.description: The number of organic searches happened in a session. This metric is search engine agnostic.

ga:browser.name: Browser
ga:browser.description: The name of users' browsers, for example, Internet Explorer or Firefox.

ga:browserVersion.name: Browser Version
ga:browserVersion.description: The version of users' browsers, for example, 2.0.0.14.

ga:operatingSystem.name: Operating System
ga:operatingSystem.description: Users' operating system, for example, Windows, Linux, Macintosh, or iOS.

ga:operatingSystemVersion.name: Operating System Version
ga:operatingSystemVersion.description: The version of users' operating system, i.e., XP for Windows, PPC for Macintosh.

ga:mobileInputSelector.name: Mobile Input Selector
ga:mobileInputSelector.description: Selector (e.g., touchscreen, joystick, clickwheel, stylus) used on the mobile device.

ga:mobileDeviceInfo.name: Mobile Device Info
ga:mobileDeviceInfo.description: The branding, model, and marketing name used to identify the mobile device.

ga:mobileDeviceMarketingName.name: Mobile Device Marketing Name
ga:mobileDeviceMarketingName.description: The marketing name used for the mobile device.

ga:deviceCategory.name: Device Category
ga:deviceCategory.description: The type of device: desktop, tablet, or mobile.

ga:browserSize.name: Browser Size
ga:browserSize.description: The viewport size of users' browsers. A session-scoped dimension, browser size captures the initial dimensions of the viewport in pixels and is formatted as width x height, for example, 1920x960.

ga:dataSource.name: Data Source
ga:dataSource.description: The data source of a hit. By default, hits sent from analytics.js are reported as "web" and hits sent from the mobile SDKs are reported as "app". These values can be overridden in the Measurement Protocol.

ga:continent.name: Continent
ga:continent.description: Users' continent, derived from users' IP addresses or Geographical IDs.

ga:subContinent.name: Sub Continent
ga:subContinent.description: Users' sub-continent, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. For example, Polynesia or Northern Europe.

ga:country.name: Country
ga:country.description: Users' country, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs.

ga:region.name: Region
ga:region.description: Users' region, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. In U.S., a region is a state, New York, for example.

ga:metro.name: Metro
ga:metro.description: The Designated Market Area (DMA) from where traffic arrived.

ga:city.name: City
ga:city.description: Users' city, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs.

ga:latitude.name: Latitude
ga:latitude.description: The approximate latitude of users' city, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. Locations north of the equator have positive latitudes and locations south of the equator have negative latitudes.

ga:longitude.name: Longitude
ga:longitude.description: The approximate longitude of users' city, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. Locations east of the prime meridian have positive longitudes and locations west of the prime meridian have negative longitudes.

ga:networkDomain.name: Network Domain
ga:networkDomain.description: The domain name of users' ISP, derived from the domain name registered to the ISP's IP address.

ga:networkLocation.name: Service Provider
ga:networkLocation.description: The names of the service providers used to reach the property. For example, if most users of the website come via the major cable internet service providers, its value will be these service providers' names.

ga:cityId.name: City ID
ga:cityId.description: Users' city ID, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. The city IDs are the same as the Criteria IDs found at https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/geoid.

ga:continentId.name: Continent ID
ga:continentId.description: Users' continent ID, derived from users' IP addresses or Geographical IDs.

ga:countryIsoCode.name: Country ISO Code
ga:countryIsoCode.description: Users' country's ISO code (in ISO-3166-1 alpha-2 format), derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. For example, BR for Brazil, CA for Canada.

ga:metroId.name: Metro Id
ga:metroId.description: The three digit Designated Market Area (DMA) code from where traffic arrived, derived from users' IP addresses or Geographical IDs.

ga:regionId.name: Region ID
ga:regionId.description: Users' region ID, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. In U.S., a region is a state, New York, for example. The region IDs are the same as the Criteria IDs listed at https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/geoid.

ga:regionIsoCode.name: Region ISO Code
ga:regionIsoCode.description: Users' region ISO code in ISO-3166-2 format, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs.

ga:subContinentCode.name: Sub Continent Code
ga:subContinentCode.description: Users' sub-continent code in UN M.49 format, derived from their IP addresses or Geographical IDs. For example, 061 for Polynesia, 154 for Northern Europe.

ga:adGroup.name: Ad Group
ga:adGroup.description: The name of the AdWords ad group.

ga:adSlot.name: Ad Slot
ga:adSlot.description: The location (Top, RHS, or not set) of the advertisement on the hosting page.

ga:adDistributionNetwork.name: Ad Distribution Network
ga:adDistributionNetwork.description: The network (Content, Search, Search partners, etc.) used to deliver the ads.

ga:adMatchType.name: Query Match Type
ga:adMatchType.description: The match type (Phrase, Exact, Broad, etc.) applied for users' search term. Ads on the content network are identified as "Content network". For details, see https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2472708?hl=en.

ga:adKeywordMatchType.name: Keyword Match Type
ga:adKeywordMatchType.description: The match type (Phrase, Exact, or Broad) applied to the keywords. For details, see https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2472708.

ga:adMatchedQuery.name: Search Query
ga:adMatchedQuery.description: The search query that triggered impressions.

ga:adPlacementDomain.name: Placement Domain
ga:adPlacementDomain.description: The domain where the ads on the content network were placed.

ga:adPlacementUrl.name: Placement URL
ga:adPlacementUrl.description: The URL where the ads were placed on the content network.

ga:adFormat.name: Ad Format
ga:adFormat.description: The AdWords ad format (Text, Image, Flash, Video, etc.).

ga:adTargetingType.name: Targeting Type
ga:adTargetingType.description: This (keyword, placement, or vertical targeting) indicates how the AdWords ads were targeted.

ga:adTargetingOption.name: Placement Type
ga:adTargetingOption.description: It is Automatic placements or Managed placements, indicating how the ads were managed on the content network.

ga:adDisplayUrl.name: Display URL
ga:adDisplayUrl.description: The URL the AdWords ads displayed.

ga:adDestinationUrl.name: Destination URL
ga:adDestinationUrl.description: The URL to which the AdWords ads referred traffic.

ga:adwordsCustomerID.name: AdWords Customer ID
ga:adwordsCustomerID.description: Customer's AdWords ID, corresponding to AdWords API AccountInfo.customerId.

ga:adwordsCriteriaID.name: AdWords Criteria ID
ga:adwordsCriteriaID.description: AdWords API Criterion.id. The geographical targeting Criteria IDs are listed at https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/geoid.

ga:adQueryWordCount.name: Query Word Count
ga:adQueryWordCount.description: The number of words in the search query.

ga:isTrueViewVideoAd.name: TrueView Video Ad
ga:isTrueViewVideoAd.description: A boolean, Yes or No, indicating whether the ad is an AdWords TrueView video ad.

ga:adClicks.name: Clicks
ga:adClicks.description: Total number of times users have clicked on an ad to reach the property.

ga:adCost.name: Cost
ga:adCost.description: Derived cost for the advertising campaign. Its currency is the one you set in the AdWords account.

ga:CTR.name: CTR
ga:CTR.description: Click-through-rate for the ad. This is equal to the number of clicks divided by the number of impressions for the ad (e.g., how many times users clicked on one of the ads where that ad appeared).

ga:costPerTransaction.name: Cost per Transaction
ga:costPerTransaction.description: The cost per transaction for the property.

ga:costPerGoalConversion.name: Cost per Goal Conversion
ga:costPerGoalConversion.description: The cost per goal conversion for the property.

ga:costPerConversion.name: Cost per Conversion
ga:costPerConversion.description: The cost per conversion (including ecommerce and goal conversions) for the property.

ga:RPC.name: RPC
ga:RPC.description: RPC or revenue-per-click, the average revenue (from ecommerce sales and/or goal value) you received for each click on one of the search ads.

ga:ROAS.name: ROAS
ga:ROAS.description: Return On Ad Spend (ROAS) is the total transaction revenue and goal value divided by derived advertising cost.
